{"article_id":"QM2CSygexF4Eabjn","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON ( ) -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"A proposal by U.S. Republicans","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"to repeal and replace the Obamacare health insurance program","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"suffered serious new setbacks within the party on Sunday ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"when Senator Ted Cruz expressed his opposition","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"and Senator Susan Collins dug in with strong criticism of the legislation .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"Two other Republican senators , John McCain and Rand Paul , already said last week","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"they would vote against the so-called Graham-Cassidy bill .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"One more \" no \" vote among Republicans would effectively kill the party ' s latest effort in their seven-year mission","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"to overturn Obamacare ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"while dealing a new blow to President Donald Trump .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , a Republican , has said","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"he \" intends \" to put the bill up for a vote this week ,","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"but he has withheld public comment over the past few days","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"as some of his rank-and-file Republicans abandoned Trump .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"interviewed on CNN ' s \" State of the Union , \"","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"reflected the uncertainty in the battle .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"\" It is going to be very close .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"I hope","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"it passes , \"","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"Phil Novack , a spokesman for Cruz , confirmed","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that the Republican senator said at an event in Texas :","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"\" Right now , they don ' t have my vote ,","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"and I don ' t think","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"they have","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"( Senator ) Mike Lee ' s vote , either . \"","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"Lee is a conservative Republican and close ally of Cruz .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"A spokesman for Lee said","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"the senator wanted \" some technical changes \" to the legislation ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"but did not provide details .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"\" We haven ' t committed to anything yet , \"","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"Conn Carroll said in an email .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Politico reported","depth":4},{"id":35,"text":"that Cruz complained","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"that the latest Obamacare repeal bill did not address his concerns","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"about bringing down the costs of healthcare .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"On Friday , news of McCain ' s opposition sent shares of health insurance companies up .","depth":4},{"id":39,"text":"Centene ended 1.6 percent higher","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"and Humana closed up 0.2 percent .","depth":5},{"id":41,"text":"Trump has pressured his fellow Republicans for quick passage on what would be his first victory on major legislation .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"All Democrats are expected to vote against it .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"But Collins , perhaps the most moderate of Republican senators , appeared poised to oppose her party ' s latest replacement plan for the Affordable Care Act , former Democratic President Barack Obama ' s signature legislative achievement .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"She , along with McCain and Alaska Senator Lisa Murkowski , voted in July against an earlier version of Obamacare repeal .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"\" It is very difficult for me to envision a scenario","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"where I would end up voting for this bill , \"","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"Collins said on CNN ' s \" State of the Union \" on Sunday ,","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"two days after saying","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"she was \" leaning against \" the legislation .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Collins said","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"her concerns centered on the impact","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"the legislation would have on the federal Medicaid program ,","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"which helps disabled children and low-income elderly people get healthcare .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"The Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"which Republicans control by 52-48 ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"faces a Saturday deadline","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"for deciding on the bill","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"under an expiring rule","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"that lets the healthcare proposal pass with just a simple majority in the 100-member chamber , instead of the 60-vote threshold","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"needed for most legislation .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Paul ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"interviewed on NBC ' s \" Meet the Press , \"","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"attacked the centerpiece of the Republican bill","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"that would have the federal government basically turn the health insurance system over to states in the form of \" block grants . \"","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"\" They could remove the block grants from it ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"and we can vote on what we actually agree on , \"","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Paul said .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"\" I can ' t in good conscience vote","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"to keep all the spending . \"","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Some key Senate Republicans were still pushing to forge ahead .","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"Senator Lindsey Graham ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"who is leading the charge on the latest version of Obamacare repeal ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"told ABC","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"he believed","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"he would have the votes","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"to pass the legislation .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"\" The only way","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"you know","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"how people will vote","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"is you have the vote , \"","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"Graham did not detail the path","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"he sees","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"to victory .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":169,"left":0,"right":168,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":168,"left":121,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":117,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":94,"right":116,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":94,"left":89,"right":93,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":89,"left":87,"right":88,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":87,"left":86,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":86,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":88,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":93,"left":90,"right":92,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":92,"left":91,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":97,"right":115,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":97,"left":95,"right":96,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":95,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":96,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":103,"right":114,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":99,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":17,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":98,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nucleari